    <descript>
      <abstract>Ozark - St. Francis National Forests stand inventory data for vegetation, maintained in polygon format. Compartment is defined as a division of forest for purposes of orientation, administration, and silvicultural operations. It is defined by permanent boundaries, of natural features or artificially marked.</abstract>
      <purpose>Ozark-St. Francis NFs use these compartment areas to subdivide smaller areas to inventory and management of the land and timber resources</purpose>
    </descript>
